image.altText: A man poses with his fist

props.synopsis: A taekwondo instructor who allegedly murdered an entire family in Sydney will face a bedside court hearing today as New South Wales police continue investigating the motive.

title.children: Taekwondo instructor expected to face bedside court hearing after he was charged with murdering family

props.synopsis: Sixty years ago, people lost their minds as the Beatles landed in Sydney. Taylor Swift is the only artist to match the hysteria

title.children: 60 years on from the Beatles touching down in Sydney, Taylor Swift inspires a similar hysteria

image.altText: a big building with balconies

props.synopsis: Residents of the uninhabitable complex in Sydney will still incur major losses, but the deal will provide some resolution nearly five years after cracks were discovered in the building.

title.children: Mascot Towers ordeal close to end after five years as multi-million payout deal agreed for unit owners

image.altText: A customer wheels a trolley past an aisle of a supermarket with ice cream in freezers.

props.synopsis: Brad Banducci is retiring as the supermarket giant announces a massive loss and faces ongoing allegations of price gouging and unfair practices with suppliers.

title.children: Woolworths denies Banducci retirement prompted by Four Corners interview walkout

props.synopsis: Brad Banducci will be remembered for his TV interview walkout, but in his years in the top job he's delivered Woolworths bumper profits, writes Four Corners' Angus Grigg and Elise Potaka.

title.children: The question I asked before the Woolworths CEO walked out on our interview was hardly a zinger

image.altText: Julian Assange holds up his fist

props.synopsis: A London court hears people living under authoritarian regimes "disappeared" after Julian Assange blended hacking with reporting, "stole vast amounts" of classified documents and published them on his WikiLeaks website.

title.children: People 'disappeared' after Assange and Wikileaks blended hacking with journalism, court hears

image.altText: A smiling woan in early middle age. She is wearing a head-covering and a singlet.

props.synopsis: Belinda Van Krevel, the sister of a man serving life sentences for two high-profile murders, has been jailed again after committing a crime with "disturbing similarities" to a previous offence.

title.children: Seaside city's dark past resurfaces as woman who had father murdered jailed for second stabbing

image.altText: A woman and three young boys sit under a tree.

props.synopsis: More than a week after deadly storms tore through Victoria, knocking out power to more than half a million customers, the lights are still out in some hard-hit areas of the state.

title.children: Victorians left in the dark after wild storms, but a permanent fix to power outages could cost billions

image.altText: Man in black shirt holds up phone for selfie

props.synopsis: Joshua Toole has been sentenced to six years' jail over his link to a commercial drug syndicate, after pleading guilty to supplying 1.9 kilograms of methamphetamine.

title.children: Meth-dealing brother of former NSW deputy premier jailed after judge hears about 'sometimes' violent upbringing

image.altText: ATO Commissioner Chris Jordan speaks at the National Press Club.

props.synopsis: Outgoing ATO boss Chris Jordan said "Australians love their work-related expense deductions" and abolishing them in favour of lower personal income tax rates "would be a big step".

title.children: Outgoing ATO boss says getting rid of work-related expense deductions could simplify the tax system — but it's 'a big step'

image.altText: Two men celebrate after winning a cricket match

props.synopsis: New Zealand set Australia an imposing total in Wellington but a mighty innings from Mitch Marsh and some final over heroics from Tim David secured the tourists an epic victory.

title.children: Tim David the hero as Australia triumph over New Zealand in last-ball thriller

image.altText: A portrait of Ewen MacIntosh in The Office.

props.synopsis: Actor Ewen MacIntosh, who was best known for playing Keith Bishop in the British comedy The Office, has died aged 50.

title.children: Ricky Gervais pays tribute to 'very funny' The Office star Ewen MacIntosh

image.altText: A Kimberley beach at sunset, with a ridge of deep orange rocks near the shoreline and purple flowering vegetation

props.synopsis: More details are emerging of how shocked locals rescued boat arrivals from the bush and why one mystery remains. What happened to the boat and how did the skipper get away?

title.children: 'Those men would have died': Inside the remote community that helped rescue 39 foreigners in Western Australia

image.altText: Four of the Eagles members with a signed guitar

props.synopsis: A criminal trial is set to open over the handwritten lyrics to the Eagles' legendary hit Hotel California.

title.children: Trial over handwritten lyrics to Hotel California set to begin

image.altText: Doctors in surgical gear performing an operation.

props.synopsis: A country NSW MP says he had been contacted by patients whose elective surgeries were suddenly cancelled by the hospital without any explanation.

title.children: Anaesthetic services suspended at regional NSW hospital after doctors found practising without proper supervision

image.altText: A woman stands behind a pub bar holding five bottles of water.

props.synopsis: A Yass pub says it's spending at least $50 a day on bottled water, while GPs are relying on hand sanitiser, as a treatment problem with the water supply remains one week on from when it started.

title.children: Yass businesses spending hundreds of dollars a week on bottled water, as treatment problem remains

image.altText: A baby's hand clenched in a fist in a bed with bumble bee printed sheets

props.synopsis: Tragedy touches a community in the Byron Shire, where two babies died after a woman went into labour at home.

title.children: Police investigate deaths of twins born at a home in Mullumbimby

image.altText: A close-up of police tape across a street.

props.synopsis: A man who killed one person and stabbed two others in the Perth suburb of Tuart Hill will be eligible for parole in 20 years, after he was sentenced to life behind bars.

title.children: Man gets 20-year minimum sentence for scissor murder of 53yo and attack on two others in drug -induced psychosis

image.altText: Andrew Denton hosts Live and Sweaty__PDP025245

props.synopsis: Award-winning ABC Sport presenter Karen Tighe announces she is leaving the organisation to focus on her health.

title.children: Celebrated broadcaster Karen Tighe farewells ABC Sport after trailblazing career in TV and radio

image.altText: Placards, balloons, flowers and a shirt hang from a tree by the side of a road.

props.synopsis: A 19-year-old pleads guilty to multiple charges over the 2022 crash in Wollongong as court documents reveal what happened on the tragic night.

title.children: 'Want to come for a drive?' Details of crash that killed 12-year-old boy revealed

image.altText: Jamahl and his mum Shanna hug in front of a rainbow wall at the school

props.synopsis: Over the years, Jamahl Ali has thrived with support from his teachers, family and therapists. Now this boy with "a very kind heart" is leading his peers at Toronto Public School.

title.children: Jamahl was non-verbal before starting kindergarten. This year he's school captain

image.altText: Night time photo of firefighter at a blaze .

props.synopsis: Crime data extracted by the ABC shows big spikes in arson offences across New South Wales, with some regional areas reporting rates up to eight times the state average.

title.children: Arson cases rise with one NSW regional town reporting rate up to eight times state average

image.altText: dampier foreshore

props.synopsis: A Perth court hears the 26-year-old man, who drove into the ocean off Dampier, was suffering psychosis and was attempting to baptise his son, not kill him.

title.children: Father who drove off pier in remote WA wanted to baptise his son, not murder him, court told

image.altText: Snowtown accomplice Mark Ray Haydon.

props.synopsis: Mark Haydon, who was convicted of seven counts of assisting the Snowtown murderers, will be sent to the Adelaide pre-release centre after being granted parole.

title.children: Snowtown accomplice Mark Ray Haydon granted parole

image.altText: A bogged four-wheel drive.

props.synopsis: Rangers say two young German tourists are "lucky to be alive" after walking for several days in the Cape York wilderness after their car became bogged because of a Google Maps error.

title.children: Google Maps error forces German tourists on survival trek with wild pigs, spiders and a croc for company

image.altText: Angus Taylor standing inside Parliament House

props.synopsis: Shadow Treasurer Angus Taylor says personal income tax has increased by a "record" 27 per cent in the first 18 months of the Albanese government.

title.children: Angus Taylor says personal income tax has increased by a 'record' 27 per cent under Labor. Is that correct?

image.altText: Two small turtles are laid next to their egg

props.synopsis: When scientists discovered seven baby Bell's turtles in a batch of six incubated eggs in the NSW Northern Tablelands recently, they were initially stumped.

title.children: Tiny endangered turtle twins hatch from same egg in 1-in-3000 event amid efforts to save the species

image.altText: A mountain biker in the wilderness.

props.synopsis: The extinct volcano in the NSW Central West was set to be reignited by a nearly 100km network of mountain bike trails, but the project has stalled indefinitely because of funding.

title.children: Plan to build mountain bike trails in extinct volcano hits roadblock, leaving riders deflated

image.altText: A creature with dozens of purple and white tentacles sitting on sand.

props.synopsis: Experts say the WA-first sighting of a rare crab and photos of a strange anemone on Broome's beaches highlight the untapped wonders off Australia's coasts.

title.children: Citizen scientists discover weird and wonderful creatures on WA coast
